&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information Analyst - Forward Thinking Birmingham&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a self-starter, who loves working with data and information and who wants to use your analytical skill set in a fascinating area of the NHS?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at Birmingham Children’s Hospital, you will work with our mental health division Forward Thinking Birmingham (FTB), providing key analytical support to management and clinical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated candidate with experience of working within an analytical role. Ideally they will have strong SQL skills and have experience using reporting tools such as SSRS.The successful candidate will be skillful at engaging with a range of different stakeholders in order to develop and implement reporting solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will contribute to contractual performance reporting and help support the development of a reporting service for FTB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent data handling skills are essential, as well as the ability to help use data to support change and illustrate performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information, please contact Katie Guy -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;katie.guy@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
